The paper deals with facial emotion recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed algorithm involves feature selection and classification, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and pattern recognition (cs.MM). The use of normalization and outlier suppression techniques also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
